cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.AI 

This paper is about social influence prediction using deep learning. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as the paper specifically focuses on social networks such as Facebook, Twitter, WeChat, and Weibo. The second likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper proposes an end-to-end framework using deep neural networks for learning users' latent feature representation. The third likely category is cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) as the paper deals with social influence prediction. The fourth likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the paper mentions online recommendation and advertising, which are related to information retrieval. The fifth likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as deep learning is a subfield of AI and the paper proposes a deep learning-based approach for social influence prediction.
